text.tspan: Tire
It’d be better to use tires which are designed
for puncture protection and durability,
e.g. Maxxis OverDrive Excel Trekking Wired Tire.
Casset & Rear Derailleurs
Adjust your cycling speeds.
it’d better to have at least 3 shifts
when you take a Cycling Around Taiwan.
Chainrings & Front Dailleur
Adjust your cycling speeds.
it’d better to have at least 7 shifts
when you take a Cycling Around Taiwan.
Frameset
Pick a size that fit your body.
When you get off the saddle and stand on ground,
there should be two fingers wide between
your crotch and the top tube of frameset.
Bicycle Carrier
For carring bicycle bagsinstead of a passenger.
You may carry one bag on each side.
Saddle
Adjust a height that fit your body.
Slight bent in the knee (25 to 35 degrees )
at the bottom of pedal stroke.
Suspension
To suspend the rider and bicycle in
order to insulate them from the
roughness of the terrain.
